## ✅ Solution 1 (BEST): On-demand Revalidation (Recommended)

### Flow

```
Admin updates product (Bagisto)
        ↓
Laravel Observer fires
        ↓
Clear Redis product cache
        ↓
Call Next.js revalidate API
        ↓
Next.js clears page cache
        ↓
Next request shows latest product
```

---

### Step 1: Next.js revalidation endpoint

```js
// app/api/revalidate/product/route.js
import { revalidatePath } from "next/cache";

export async function POST(req) {
  const { productId, secret } = await req.json();

  if (secret !== process.env.REVALIDATE_SECRET) {
    return Response.json({ message: "Unauthorized" }, { status: 401 });
  }

  revalidatePath(`/products/${productId}`);
  revalidatePath(`/products`);

  return Response.json({ revalidated: true });
}
```

---

### Step 2: Laravel Bagisto Product Observer

```php
use Illuminate\Support\Facades\Http;
use Illuminate\Support\Facades\Redis;

class ProductObserver
{
    public function saved($product)
    {
        // 1️⃣ Clear Redis
        Redis::del("product:{$product->id}");
        Redis::del("products:list");

        // 2️⃣ Tell Next.js to revalidate
        Http::post(env('NEXT_REVALIDATE_URL'), [
            'productId' => $product->id,
            'secret' => env('NEXT_REVALIDATE_SECRET'),
        ]);
    }
}
```

---

### Step 3: Environment variables

**Laravel `.env`**

```env
NEXT_REVALIDATE_URL=https://frontend.com/api/revalidate/product
NEXT_REVALIDATE_SECRET=supersecret
```

**Next.js `.env`**

```env
REVALIDATE_SECRET=supersecret
```

